In .NET MAUI, use the **Lifecycle events** API in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup) to hook into platform-specific events:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is pausing
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // runs when app is no longer visible
        }));
#elif IOS
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // runs when app enters background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.
- On Android, `OnPause` fires when the activity loses focus; `OnStop` fires when it's no longer visible.
- On iOS, `DidEnterBackground` fires when the app moves to the background.
- Use `#if` directives so platform code only compiles for the target platform.

This approach keeps lifecycle handling in one place without needing custom platform renderers or native code files.
